Of the treatment of hemorrhoids	On cauterization for anal haemorrhoids.	0.5041495
When the hemorrhoids are in the anus, one or more, and are old and consist of large cold and moist corrupted humors, and are treated as we have described in divisions/sections, and it is not effective, then make cauteries: Three on the spine, the one that is furthest outside, beneath the shoulder blade little by little in a triangular shape, and one cautery below the navel two fingers;	When there are one or more chronic haemorrhoids in the anus arising from thick and cold humours or corrupt humidities, and they have been treated by those measures mentioned in the section, without effect, then sear the patient with three cauterizations over the lowest dorsal vertebra a little below the flat part of the back, triangularly; and one about two fingers' breadth below the navel.	0.80113196
And if you think that his stomach is chilled, and the food does not digest, and one sees swelling in the face, then make a large cautery on the stomach, as mentioned before, and another on the liver, and another on the spleen with the key-shaped cautery; and leave the cautery open for a long time. After, treat the area until it is healed.	And if you consider that his stomach has become chilled and his food not being digested, and you see his face swollen, then do one big cauterization over the stomach as previously described; and one over his liver; and another over the spleen; with the claviform cautery. Keep the burn open a long while; then dress till healed.	0.9365137
